def: A swallowing up as if in a gulf. [R.]
Bidding farewell; suitable or designed for an occasion ofleave-taking; as, a valedictory oration.
A regulus consisting essentially of nickel, obtained as aresidue in fusing cobalt and nickel ores with silica and sodiumcarbonate to make smalt.
The office or position of an envoy.
A disaccharide present in glycosides. Prepared from rutin byhydrolysis with rhamnodiastase. 6-O-a-L-rhamnosyl-D-glucose;C12H22O10.
A long rope or chain by which an animal is fastened, as to astake, so that it can range or feed only within certain limits.
the yarn or thread of any stuff of which the strands of a ropeare made.
